    <p>{`Create a VPC, give is a name tag, the CIDR block is the network range eg. `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`10.17.0.0/16`}</inlineCode>{` (16 is as large as we can make our VPC) and we can choose the VPC to be `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Default`}</inlineCode>{` or `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Dedicated`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`Once the instance config is up, we can choose `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Actions > Edit DHCP Options`}</inlineCode>{` which will edit how those addresses/options are set. Currently the /16 address range will be `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`10.17.0.1`}</inlineCode>{` but the config will basically assign ranges between .2 and .253. We can change that range with `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`DHCP Options Set`}</inlineCode>{` if we want to.`}</p>
