    <p>{`At the IP itself, we can see that the website is now running, but the second instance isn't running the container... why? Because it is a cluster. Even though we have two INSTANCES running we only configured ONE service running ONE task with ONE task definition.`}</p>
    <p>{`A lot of this is because we haven't set the ELB. Since we didn't add a ELB, we will only see the container on the first EC2 we launched.`}</p>
