    <p>{`What we have to do in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`EC2 > Load Balancers > Status`}</inlineCode>{`, we click on it and edit the instances. The the ELB has already registered that there is another container instance (as you'll be able to see) so we click on it and then we select save.`}</p>
    <p>{`Now we have multiple nodes, and the ELB will now use round robin to choose the node to use.`}</p>
    <p>{`Load balancers do not currently store session state by default, which can be a trouble if you are running with round robin. You need to turn on Stickiness on the Port Configuration in order to keep sessions.`}</p>
    <p>{`We can enabled `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Load Balancer`}</inlineCode>{` generated cookies or appliation generated cookie stickiness. Application will look for a cookie you set.`}</p>
    <p>{`Generally you just want 5 minutes or so or you could suffer from `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`affinity overload`}</inlineCode>{` if one server gets overloaded.`}</p>
